cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.RO 

The paper deals with computer vision and machine learning techniques for detecting and separating multiple people in images, which falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also proposes an optimization approach to solve the region assembly problem, which involves combinatorial optimization and constraint satisfaction, and uses deep learning techniques for semantic segmentation and object proposal generation, which are relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates its method on three challenging datasets, which involves performance evaluation and benchmarking, and demonstrates its impact on a proxemics recognition task, which involves robotics and human-robot interaction, and thus may also fall under the categories of multimedia (cs.MM) and robotics (cs.RO).
